    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, most ARM loans include protective features like periodic payment caps (often limiting increases by 2–6% per year) and lifetime caps on how much the total rate can ever exceed the initial rate. Without these limits, your payment could indeed spike uncontrollably during the first five years if market rates surge dramatically. To determine if the lower starting rate is worth the risk, you should calculate a \"break-even point\" based on your projected rate adjustments versus savings.",
